The concept of a \'93single economic entity\'94 seems to have found its way into the matter in an affidavit filed by Appellant and deposed to by one, Calvyn Michael Du Toit who describes himself as \'93a part-time Professor of Business Economics, lecturing to and guiding students in their post graduates studies on a free-lance basis at various higher education institutions.\'94 }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
In the heads of argument filed on behalf of Appellant , it is submitted that Professor Du Toit is correct when he says \'93}{\i\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
that the Articles of Association of the Respondent essentially constitute a voluntary agreement between farmers or producers of citrus to jointly pack and market their fruit through the Respondent as a vehicle in order to manage the packing and marketing facilities on a more economical basis. The members accordingly form a single economic entity insofar as the packing and marketing of their fruit are}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\lang2057
