in sub-section 4(1). Implicit in the reasoning underlying Section 4(5) is the notion that firms cannot conspire with \'91themselves\'92. In insisting that the respondent and its members do not }
\par \pard\plain \s21\sb0\sa120\qj{\b\rtlch \ltrch\loch
have a separate existence, the respondent is effectively proposing that we import the reasoning underlying Sub-section 4(5) to a consideration under Section 8 \'96 it employs this section }
