Our Courts have repeatedly stated that where proceedings are conducted informally or in an inquisitorial manner the decision maker is placed in an active role to get at the truth and that the ordinary rules of evidence do not apply.\~  Subject at all times to the requirements of fairness, the Tribunal is not precluded from having regard to hearsay evidence.\~  (See: }{\i\rtlch \ltrch\loch
